# agent-compose: From Config to Running Agent
Set Shell "bash"
Set Theme "iterm"
Set Title "agent-compose"
Set WindowBar false
Set FontSize 16
Set Width 110
Set Height 60
Set TypingSpeed 30ms
Set WaitDuration 2s
Set Prompt "\[\033[1;32m\]➜\[\033[0m\]  \[\033[1;36m\]\W\[\033[0m\] \[\033[1;36m\]git:(\[\033[31m\]$(git symbolic-ref --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo '-')\[\033[1;36m\])\[\033[0m\] \[\033[33m\]✗\[\033[0m\] "

Narrate "agent-compose declares what an AI agent needs and runs it in a governed OpenShell sandbox. One command, zero infrastructure."
Type "./ac --help"
Enter
Sleep 2s
Wait

Clear
Narrate "ac doctor validates your entire setup: runtimes, inference providers, MCP servers, skills, and the OpenShell gateway."
Type "./ac doctor 2>&1 | head -50"
Enter
Sleep 3s
Wait

Clear
Narrate "Agents are declared in config.yaml. A runtime, inference provider, MCP servers, skills, and a prompt."
Type "grep -A 10 '^agents:' ~/.ac/config.yaml"
Enter
Sleep 2s
Wait

Clear
Narrate "ac get resolves all layers into a complete sandbox spec: image, env vars, egress endpoints, tools, and providers."
Type "./ac get security-reviewer --json | jq '{name, image, providers, env: (.env | keys), egress, tools}'"
Enter
Sleep 3s
Wait

Clear
Narrate "ac run creates the sandbox, applies egress policy, injects credentials, executes the agent, and cleans up. All streamed in real time."
Type "./ac run quick-review --prompt 'What is 2+2? Reply with just the number.' --dry-run"
Enter
Sleep 4s
Wait

Clear
Narrate "Every sandbox gets a deny-by-default network policy. Only declared endpoints are reachable. Credentials never touch agent code."
Type "./ac run security-reviewer --dry-run 2>/dev/null | grep -E 'policy|endpoint|binary'"
Enter
Sleep 3s
Wait

Clear
Narrate "Same engine powers CLIs, dashboards, and pipelines. Import as a Go library. One API everywhere."
Type "echo 'Declare it. Resolve it. Run it. github.com/zanetworker/agent-compose'"
Enter
Sleep 2s
